      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JAYASHREE (3) got well back on resumption but closed off strongly to finish 2.6L off the winner over 1200m here. The rise in trip won't pose an issue and the better draw today should see her be closer in the run. Nottle remains on board and she can end her winning drought. SPANGLEDSTAR (5) flew home from the back of the pack last start over 1300m to be 2.2L off the winner with no weight on her back. She'll carry more weight today, but she rates highly on her recent form and she'll be strong late in the race once again. BONDI'S SON (8) is racing well in recent events. He's likely to end up back in the pack on settling, but the rise in trip suits and he can put his best foot forward. COULDABEENAHANDBAG (7) was solid when on the speed over 1100m last start and steps out to 1400m now. Worth plenty of thought. WHATYOUTALKINBOUT (4) is better than he showed last time out and can improve third-up into the campaign.",
